## Problema 4

4. In “zero-g” airplane rides, passengers can float around the cabin, as if they were weightless. A flight
trajectory for such a ride is shown below, with a few points during the journey labelled. Which of
the following statements is correct? Take $\vec{a}$ to be the acceleration of the plane during the “zero-g”
part of the flight.
(A) The “zero-g” flight begins at a and ends at c, during which $|\vec{a}| = g$ and $\vec{a}$ points up.
(B) The “zero-g” flight begins at a and ends at e, during which $|\vec{a}| = 0$.
(C) The “zero-g” flight begins at b and ends at d, during which $|\vec{a}| = g$ and $\vec{a}$ points down.
(D) The “zero-g” flight begins at c and ends at e, during which $|\vec{a}| = g$ and $\vec{a}$ points down.
(E) The “zero-g” flight begins at d and ends at e, during which $|\vec{a}| = 0$.

<!--fig:start-->
![[_attachments/2020_Fma_B/2020_Fma_B_p3_f2.png]]
*grafico altitudine vs tempo aereo zero-g*
<!--fig:end-->

