## Problema 5

5. A mote of dust is initially located at distance $R$ from the sun, which has mass $M$. At this point,
the mote has a small tangential velocity $v$. Which of the following is a good approximation for the
distance of closest subsequent approach between the mote and the sun?
(A) $\dfrac{R^3v^4}{G^2M^2}$
(B) $\dfrac{R^3v^4}{2G^2M^2}$
(C) $\dfrac{R^2v^2}{2GM}$
(D) $\dfrac{R^2v^2}{GM}$
(E) $\dfrac{2R^2v^2}{GM}$

<!--fig:start-->
![[_attachments/2020_Fma_B/2020_Fma_B_p3_f3.png]]
*schema sole-granello con M, v, R*
<!--fig:end-->

**Topic:** [[Gravitation]]
**Metodi:** [[Conservation Laws (metodo)|Conservation Laws]], [[Approximation & Series Expansion (metodo)|Approximation & Series Expansion]], [[Newton's Law of Gravitation (metodo)|Newton's Law of Gravitation]]
**Competenze:** [[Mathematical Modeling (competenza)|Mathematical Modeling]], [[Physical Reasoning (competenza)|Physical Reasoning]]
