## Problema 15

15. In the device shown, blocks of various masses are placed on pistons so that the device is in equilibrium. (The fluid in the drawing is to scale.) There are valves that are both initially open at
locations A and B. One of the valves is closed, and the system is allowed to come to equilibrium.
How will this affect the height of the mass $m_2$?
(A) Closing either valve will have no effect on the height of $m_2$.
(B) Closing either valve causes $m_2$ to rise.
(C) Closing either valve causes $m_2$ to fall.
(D) Closing valve A causes $m_2$ to rise, and closing valve B causes $m_2$ to fall.
(E) Closing valve A causes $m_2$ to fall, and closing valve B causes $m_2$ to rise.

