18. An extendable arm is made from rigid beams free to pivot around the dots shown. Spring 1, with
equilibrium length $L_1$, is attached between points A and C while spring 2, with equilibrium length
$L_2$ is attached between B and D. The system is allowed to come to equilibrium. In equilibrium,
what is the ratio of the tension in spring 1 to the tension in spring 2?
(A) $-2/3$
(B) $-3/4$
(C) $-1$
(D) $-3/2$
(E) There is not enough information to determine the ratio.

